         <abstract>
            <p>Some results are obtained concerning the signs of the coefficients in the expansions in powers of $x^{-1}, (1 + x)^{-1}$ or $(1 - x)^{-1}$ of $1/p_n(x)$ and $q_n(x)$, where $p_n(x)$ is the polynomial of degree $n$ in the orthogonal sequence associated with a given weight-function $w(x)$ over $(-1, 1)$ and $q_n(x) = \int^1_{-1}w(t)p_n(t)(x - t)^{-1} dt$.</p>
          </abstract>
